[html lang=en
  [head
    [meta charset=utf-8]
    [meta name=viewport content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"]
    [title Experience — Sergey Denisov]
    [link rel=icon type=image/png href=icon.png]
    [link rel=stylesheet href=site.css]
    [script src=https://unpkg.com/lucide@latest/dist/umd/lucide.min.js]
  ]
  [body
    [header :site-header data-screen-label=Header
      [:shell
        [a :wordmark href=index.html aria-label=Home
          [span :dot]
          [span Sergey Denisov]
        ]
        [nav :nav aria-label=Primary
          [a href=index.html | Home]
          [a :is-active href=projects.html | Experience]
          [a href=blog.html | Blog]
          [a href=about.html | About]
          [a href=contact.html | Contact]
        ]
      ]
    ]
    [main data-screen-label=Experience
      [:shell
        [:page-stack
          [:page-head
            [:eyebrow | // experience]
            [h1 :title | Systems, finance, and responsibility]
            [p :lede | Most of my work has lived in trading, backend-heavy distributed systems, messaging, APIs, and the steady delivery of reliable code.]
          ]
          [section :experience
            [article :experience-item
              [:experience-head
                [
                  [h2 Gemini Crypto Exchange]
                  [p :experience-role | Staff Software Engineer · Order Management]
                ]
                [:experience-meta
                  [span Remote (US)]
                  [span :tnum | 2022 – Feb 2026]
                ]
              ]
              [p :experience-summary | Crypto exchange and custodian supporting spot and derivatives trading, equities, and event contracts.]
              [p :experience-env
                [strong Environment:]
                Scala, Go, Python, TypeScript, React, Kafka, Bazel, gRPC (Protobuf), PostgreSQL, Redis, Kubernetes (EKS), AWS, Terraform, Helm, Docker, Harness, Jenkins, GitHub Actions, Claude Code
              ]
              [ul :experience-points
                [li Led a team of 4 engineers; owned execution, code quality, and mentoring.]
                [li Top-10 GitHub contributor in the company monorepo.]
                [li Led migration from hardcoded asset and instrument definitions to service-driven dynamic configuration, updating SBE message schemas, evolving database schemas, and modifying large parts of the monorepo while maintaining production stability. Built TypeScript self-serve admin tooling with validation and audit trails so business users could safely manage assets and instruments without engineering involvement.]
                [li Implemented dynamic instrument restrictions at scale for 5,000 instruments and 300K restrictions: integrated a new restrictions service, introduced business-entity–based rules, added caching for efficient evaluation, and migrated legacy logic. Delivered admin tooling with a React UI and audit history that removed SQL from the restriction update workflow and enabled self-serve availability management. Added Slack notifications for change visibility.]
                [li Built incentives and leaderboards backend for derivatives trading with reproducible computations, eligibility logic, and auditable outputs: scheduled winner selection, P&L and ROI aggregation, notifications, and REST APIs consumed by the UI.]
                [li Contributed to Gemini’s Settlement Engine, enabling complex multi-asset clearing between institutional counterparties, and maintained the legacy Gemini Clearing Engine.]
                [li Improved order lifecycle flows and onboarding by building and maintaining customer-facing REST APIs across order and institutional client pipelines, including ledger interactions for tracking transaction state and account balances.]
                [li Delivered internal admin tools including bulk credit issuance used for asset delistings and customer offboarding; recognized by department leadership for streamlining operations.]
                [li Deployed microservices to Kubernetes on EKS by updating Helm charts and releasing via Harness CI/CD. Supported safe rollouts as a release pilot engineer for customer-facing services.]
                [li Developed and owned Datadog dashboards, monitors, and runbooks for order-ingress pipelines, improving detection and remediation of production issues.]
              ]
            ]
            [article :experience-item
              [:experience-head
                [
                  [h2 Morgan Stanley]
                  [p :experience-role | Vice President / Senior Software Engineer · Credit Derivatives]
                ]
                [:experience-meta
                  [span New York, NY]
                  [span :tnum | 2015 – 2022]
                ]
              ]
              [p :experience-summary | Tradeflow: CDS ledger and lifecycle platform for credit derivatives, used by Operations and integrated with client trading and settlement systems across New York, London, and Hong Kong.]
              [p :experience-env
                [strong Environment:]
                Java 8, Scala, C#, Akka Streams, Kafka, Sybase, Spring, Gradle, Git
              ]
              [ul :experience-points
                [li Built a Scala bridge to feed trade data from a legacy Java trading system into a next-generation Scala risk platform using Akka Streams and Kafka.]
                [li Delivered Book Move automation for moving thousands to tens of thousands of trades: automated account adjustments, fee-trade generation, and reporting. Implemented a two-phase rollout culminating in redesigned accounting behavior that retained realized payments and moved only unrealized ones, reducing operational risk.]
                [li Overhauled Credit Event Management tooling for hard credit events: improved trade eligibility discovery, reference entity and portfolio version updates, and fee application. Reduced execution time and eliminated routine developer involvement.]
                [li Re-architected synchronization of back-to-back trades with parent trades; reduced incidents from 2–3 per week to roughly 1–2 every 6 months, with the remaining issues largely unrelated to sync logic.]
                [li Implemented workflow and state-machine updates for new business requirements, and enhanced trade maturation reporting and batch workflows.]
                [li Drove stability improvements through server-side support and defect reduction, shifting support rotations from high-volume firefighting to mostly integration-related issues.]
              ]
            ]
            [article :experience-item
              [:experience-head
                [
                  [h2 Markit (now part of S&P Global)]
                  [p :experience-role | Vice President / Senior Software Engineer]
                ]
                [:experience-meta
                  [span New York, NY]
                  [span :tnum | 2009 – 2015]
                ]
              ]
              [p :experience-summary | Lead developer on Genpact KYC Services and Markit Hub, spanning secure portals, APIs, SSO, publishing pipelines, partner integrations, and reliability improvements.]
              [p :experience-env
                [strong Environment:]
                Java 7, Oracle, Tomcat, Spring Core, Spring MVC, Spring Security, Spring OAuth, Thymeleaf, AngularJS, JavaScript, Maven, Subversion
              ]
              [ul :experience-points
                [li Led development on Genpact KYC Services: a secure portal, API workflows, and integration services for KYC data and subscriptions.]
                [li Led development on Markit Hub: a financial content aggregation and SSO platform with provider integrations and publishing pipelines across SOAP, CSV, and RSS feeds.]
                [li Drove platform migrations and reliability improvements across multiple internal and partner-facing services.]
              ]
            ]
          ]
          [section :section
            [:section-head
              [h2 Education]
            ]
            [:prose
              [p
                [strong Master of Science, Computer Systems Analysis]
                · Pacific National University, Russia
              ]
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ]
    ]
    [footer :site-footer
      [:shell
        [span :colophon | © 2026 Sergey Denisov]
        [:links
          [a href=https://github.com/sergey5d target=_blank rel=noreferrer | github]
          [a href=https://www.linkedin.com/in/sadenisov/ target=_blank rel=noreferrer | linkedin]
          [a href=contact.html | more →]
        ]
      ]
    ]
    [script lucide.createIcons();]
  ]
]
